      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh convergence study performed using three structured hexahedral meshes (2.1M, 6.4M, 14.8M cells) following ASME V&V 20 GCI methodology. Grid convergence index for NIH < 2.8% and for pump head < 1.9% on the medium mesh. Richardson extrapolation applied; apparent order of convergence p=1.92, consistent with second-order scheme. Fine mesh selected for all production runs.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/discretization-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "At MRL 2, a mesh convergence study with at least two refinement levels and GCI < 5% for the primary QoI is required. Achieved: three-level GCI study with GCI(NIH) = 2.8% and GCI(head) = 1.9%, both below the 5% threshold. Apparent order consistent with solver scheme order."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM) are documented in the FDA benchmark protocol and reproduced in CFD boundary conditions. Fluid properties (bovine blood analog, viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s, density 1056 kg/m³) match the experimental fluid within stated tolerances. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream pipe measurements.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/test-conditions",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "At MRL 2, test conditions must be documented and CFD boundary conditions must demonstrably correspond to the experimental setup. Achieved: full boundary condition table provided in simulation record SR-2024-007, cross-referenced to FDA benchmark protocol FY2013-0001."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of CFD outputs to experimental data performed for pump head (4.2% mean error), flow rate (boundary condition match), and NIH (12% mean relative error within experimental uncertainty band). Comparison metrics include normalized RMS error and Bland-Altman analysis. All five operating points fall within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bands.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/output-comparison",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "At MRL 2, quantitative output comparison with documented metrics is required. Acceptance threshold: CFD predictions within combined uncertainty band (experimental ± numerical) for all primary QoIs at all operating points. Achieved: all five operating points satisfy this criterion for both pump head and NIH."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which is the clinically and regulatorily accepted metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment per ASTM F1841. The relative hemolysis index (RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate < 1) is the direct decision criterion. Secondary QoI (pump head) provides hydraulic performance context. Both QoIs are directly linked to the intended use decision.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/qoi-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "At MRL 2, the QoIs must be explicitly linked to the clinical/regulatory decision criterion. Achieved: NIH is the ASTM F1841 standard metric; RH < 1 is the acceptance criterion directly mapped to the COU decision."
      }
    },
    {
