      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty propagation is not required at Model Risk Level 2. Key inputs (fluid viscosity, density, rotational speed, flow rate) are treated as deterministic values matched to experimental conditions. Input sensitivity is qualitatively addressed through the discretization error study and operating point sweep. Full UQ propagation is reserved for MRL 3 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4."
